The self-intelligent one imitates the flight of the bumblebee 
Which would it be the best method to develop technologies in order to avoid collisions, if not the imitation of the sensors of existing obstacles in the nature? 
For example that of the bumblebees. 
In a surprising project presented in the CEATEC of Japan, the bumblebees gave the starting point for the engineers of Nissan to design the following generation of the system of prevention of the collisions. 
The Nissan, in cooperation with the University of Tokyo, designed the system of robotic direction of cars type BR23C imitator of the nature, to which the characteristics of the bumblebees they gave him, with the final objective to create a system that can avoid all the collisions. 
During the flight each bumblebee creates its own oval private space that in reality a striking resemblance to our protective capsule of security bears - explained in the exposition Kazuhhiro Doi, technological director of RP and of development and investigations. 
They play an important role the composed eyes of the bumblebees that are capable of seeing in all the directions in an angle over 300 degrees. 
To copy the function of the composed eyes, the engineers utilized the system of measurement of the length by laser beams. 
This it identifies the obstacles in front of the BR23C inside a distance of 2 meters, in an angle of 180 degrees, calculates its distance and sends a sign to the microprocessor of the vehicle that immediately is transformed into a maneuver to avoid the collision. 
In a fraction of seconds the obstacle is identified, then the robot of the vehicle imitating the movements of the bumblebees, modifies the direction rotating in the necessary measure the wheels. 
As opposed to any existing system at present, this maneuver is completely instinctive. 
"If it was not thus, the robot of the vehicle would not be able to react with the sufficient rapidity as to avoid the obstacles" - explains Toshiyuki Andoh, leader of the Laboratory of Mobility and of the project of the robot of vehicles. 
It should react immediately and in instinctive form, since this technology corresponds to the most vulnerable interior layer of the protective capsule of security, in a layer inside which at present inevitable all kinds of collisions are considered. 
All the process should reflect what does a bumblebee to avoid other bumblebees. 
This process should be carried out in a to open and to close the eyes. 
Nevertheless, as opposed to the bumblebees, the movement cannot be directed up, downward or diagonal, but only can be two-dimensional and exclusively in the direction of turn of the wheels 
In this manner, instead of the infinite possibilities that exist for the bumblebees to avoid other bumblebees, here only they utilized as possibility for the robot of the car the movement newspaper and the acceleration besides the frenaje. 
The BR23C utilizes batteries of lítio-polymer that are lighter and is greater its density of energy, what means that they have a more long duration of life than that of lítio-ión. 
According to Andoh, what is important is the instinctive and intelligent reaction and not the capacity of prosecution of the data, neither much less that of storage. 
This apparatus in each second only should process some signs of entrance and to react according to the case. 
It is not necessary to store these data neither to react with an instinctive logic based on the data of the previous maneuvers, thus utilizes only some scores of kilobytes by memory. 
Themselves not memories of gigabytes are needed, neither of megabytes. 
This it is the first step to develop the technology for avoid immediately the obstacles, which according to calculations of the Nissan, inside ten years will be able to be incorporated to the models manufactured in series. 
Another possibility for its application is to incorporate the unit to the system of navigation by satellite way GPS to carry the conductor to its destiny, avoiding the existing obstacles in its road. 
